get help:

    $ celery worker --help
    $ celery worker -h

---

examples:

    $ celery worker -A celery_app -l info
    $ celery worker --app=celery_app --loglevel=INFO

    $ celery worker 
        -A <module>:<appname>
        --loglevel <level> | -l <level>
        --logfile <file> | -f <file>
---

- set celery application:
    -A celery_app 
    --app=celery_app

- set log level
    -l info
    --loglevel=INFO

    choose from: INFO|DEBUG|WARNING|ERROR|CRITICAL|FATAL

- run the celery beat periodic task scheduler (there must only be one instance of this service).

    -B
    --beat

- set a hostname

    -n
    --hostname=HOSTNAME

- path to schedule database if running with the -B option. Defaults to celerybeat-schedule.

    -s SCHEDULE_FILENAME
    --schedule=SCHEDULE_FILENAME

- set use id, group id, or user name of the user to run as after detaching

    --uid=UID
    --gid=GID
